    {
      "id": "7ba1ae1ec70380a3b8c5546eb390c45a0bae3051",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-13 13:19:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(6 inline comments)\n\n-1 only until the compact/compat issues are either fixed or explained.\n\nNot really related to this patch, but it would be really good to understand why lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4 is not the same on b2_1 and master.  That of course could be handled in a separate issue, assuming it's not affecting the detection and building of both new and old OFED packaging.\n\nWorth noting the successful build only proves no regression.  There's no proof (in the form of a build) that the new OFED packaging is handled by this code.  The same is true of the original patch on master however.\n\nIt probably should have been done on the original patch, but it might be good to change the OFED version for a supported platform to the new version and make sure it builds also.  Not a requirement for a +1, but it would be useful all the same.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
